✅ Ultimate Stock Analyzer - Requirements
🧱 1️⃣ Python Version

Python 3.7 or above (Recommended: Python 3.10)

📚 2️⃣ Python Libraries (Install via pip)
pip install yfinance pandas matplotlib numpy

🗂️ 3️⃣ File Structure Example
ultimate_stock_analyzer/
│
├── ultimate_stock_analyzer.py    ← (Your main script file)
│
├── other files (optional)

✅ 4️⃣ Internet Connection Required

✅ Data will be fetched live from Yahoo Finance (using yfinance library).

Make sure system is connected to the internet while running the program.

🚀 5️⃣ How It Works

User provides stock symbol (e.g., RELIANCE.NS, AAPL, ^NSEI).

User provides time period (like 1M, 1Y, MAX).

Data downloaded via yfinance → Analyzed → Professional charts generated (price, volume, returns, volatility, support/resistance, correlation heatmap).

Data not stored permanently, shown during execution.

✅ 6️⃣ Optional (Examples of Symbols You Can Try)
Category	Example Symbols
Indian Stocks	RELIANCE.NS, TCS.NS
US Stocks	AAPL, TSLA, MSFT
Indian Indices	^NSEI, ^BSESN, ^NSEBANK
Global Indices	^GSPC, ^DJI, ^IXIC
ETFs	GOLDBEES.NS, SPY, QQQ
Commodities	GC=F (Gold), SI=F (Silver)
Crypto	BTC-USD, ETH-USD, DOGE-USD
⚡️ 7️⃣ Run Command
python ultimate_stock_analyzer.py

✅ 8️⃣ Final Notes

No external dataset required, live data fetching.

Make sure matplotlib can display plots (GUI environment needed).

Internet is mandatory during execution.

Optional: Run inside a virtual environment for isolation.
